Yes.  That was a DeliberateLazyMoment 
(http://c2.com/cgi/wiki?DeliberateLazyMoment), as my follow-up might 
suggest.  I actually don&#39;t remember a time when I have tested for 
instanceof or isInstance(), although it&#39;s possible I have.  I usually 
test the getMessage() to make sure it references my &quot;inputs&quot;.

A common example might be something like:

public void testInstantiation() {
    try {
        ApplicationConfiguration.instanceFor(badParameter(...), 
goodParameter(...));
        fail(&quot;should have thrown IllegalArgumentException because 
&lt;exceptionReason dealing with badParameter&gt;&quot;);
    } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {
        assertStringContains(e.getMessage(), &lt;exceptionReason dealing 
with badParameter&gt;);
    }
    try {
        ApplicationConfiguration.instanceFor(goodParameter(...), 
badParameter(...));
        fail(&quot;should have thrown IllegalArgumentException because 
&lt;exceptionReason dealing with badParameter&gt;&quot;);
    } catch (IllegalArgumentException e) {
        assertStringContains(e.getMessage(), &lt;exceptionReason dealing 
with badParameter&gt;);
    }

assertNotNull(ApplicationConfiguration.instanceFor(goodParameter(...), 
goodParameter(...)));
}

